   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <note class="- topic/note ">The main battery cabinet has side panels and a temperature
sensor installed. The adjacent battery cabinets have no side panels
or temperature sensors installed. The main battery cabinet must always
be installed to the left with the adjacent battery cabinet(s) to the
right.</note>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the right side panel from the main battery cabinet
and install it on the right side of the rightmost adjacent battery
cabinet.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/gupxcab600iec_preparemovesidepanel_w120mm_0000151271.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Line up the battery cabinets with the main battery cabinet
to the left.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Install interconnection brackets on all the battery cabinets.
Use C-clamps to hold the battery cabinets together to make the installation
easier. Install two interconnection brackets in the front and two
interconnection brackets in the rear. Use four screws on each side
of each interconnection bracket to fasten it to the battery cabinets.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig expanse="page" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <title class="- topic/title ">Front View of the Battery Cabinets with Interconnection Brackets</title>
                  <image href="../Images/battery_cabinet_800mm_three_cabinets_interconnected_120mm_0000153242.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
      </steps>
